1
00:01:05,250 --> 00:01:06,582
Master Jan...

2
00:01:09,250 --> 00:01:10,457
Master Jan!

3
00:01:16,583 --> 00:01:17,666
Ken!

4
00:01:18,750 --> 00:01:22,916
When did you get here?

5
00:01:23,792 --> 00:01:27,749
You were asleep,
I didn't want to wake you.

6
00:01:28,583 --> 00:01:32,957
I wasn't sleeping,

7
00:01:33,917 --> 00:01:36,082
I was just thinking.

8
00:01:36,375 --> 00:01:38,749
What's on your mind?

9
00:01:41,083 --> 00:01:45,207
Old men like us can only think
about one thing...

10
00:01:45,583 --> 00:01:48,124
The past.

11
00:01:52,083 --> 00:01:56,166
Jan Dara is still Jan Dara.

12
00:01:56,542 --> 00:01:59,041
Ken is still Ken.

13
00:01:59,667 --> 00:02:01,582
We've just got so old.

14
00:02:01,708 --> 00:02:02,791
Yes.

15
00:02:03,083 --> 00:02:05,124
We're very old.

16
00:02:06,250 --> 00:02:10,124
But my heart... my heart refuses to age.

17
00:02:10,500 --> 00:02:14,999
I still remember the love of my life,
Hyacinth.

18
00:02:15,083 --> 00:02:18,916
I still remember Madame Boonleung,
always so graceful.

19
00:02:19,625 --> 00:02:22,791
I still remember that perverse woman,
Miss Kaew.

20
00:02:23,792 --> 00:02:26,291
I even remember someone
we both knew very well.

21
00:02:26,417 --> 00:02:27,582
Would you like an inhalant?

22
00:02:27,708 --> 00:02:28,916
No.

23
00:02:30,333 --> 00:02:32,916
I still remember Saisoi,
Kaew's maidservant

24
00:02:33,000 --> 00:02:38,166
and your first woman.

25
00:02:40,167 --> 00:02:42,541
She Was your first too.

26
00:02:44,500 --> 00:02:47,582
Right,
we shared the same property back then.

27
00:02:52,083 --> 00:02:55,041
Ken, the inhalant please!

28
00:03:01,625 --> 00:03:03,625
Do you remember the exact date
when we left Bangkok

29
00:03:04,083 --> 00:03:09,874
for my grandmother's house in Phijit?

30
00:03:10,875 --> 00:03:16,582
It was ages ago!
Who would remember that?

31
00:03:17,917 --> 00:03:21,082
I do. I'll never forget it.

32
00:03:21,917 --> 00:03:28,499
It was December 10, 1932.

33
00:03:29,250 --> 00:03:34,082
The day
the king granted the constitution.

34
00:03:56,333 --> 00:03:59,749
Master Jan,
Madame is waiting for you in the house.

35
00:04:00,333 --> 00:04:01,291
All right.

36
00:04:44,292 --> 00:04:46,916
My dearest Jan...

37
00:04:49,417 --> 00:04:55,291
My precious!

38
00:04:57,833 --> 00:05:02,291
Are you Ken, son of Poom?

39
00:05:03,333 --> 00:05:04,374
Yes, ma'am.

40
00:05:05,500 --> 00:05:07,416
I know everything.

41
00:05:07,958 --> 00:05:11,082
Wad sent a telegraph this morning

42
00:05:11,583 --> 00:05:14,832
to tell me the whole story.

43
00:05:16,333 --> 00:05:18,749
My dearest Jan...

44
00:05:19,750 --> 00:05:22,416
Forgive me for putting you

45
00:05:22,708 --> 00:05:25,791
through all the misfortunes.

46
00:05:26,583 --> 00:05:30,416
It's all because I chose a wrong man

47
00:05:31,083 --> 00:05:33,916
to be your mother's husband.

48
00:05:39,833 --> 00:05:43,749
Wisnan was working at the Palace Office.

49
00:05:44,042 --> 00:05:47,624
He was also an accomplished court actor.

50
00:05:47,958 --> 00:05:50,291
Even I was fooled by his theatrics.

51
00:05:50,500 --> 00:05:53,666
It never occurred to me that

52
00:05:53,750 --> 00:06:01,332
he would put on a realistic performance
in life as he did on stage.

53
00:06:01,583 --> 00:06:05,791
So I made him marry Dara, your mother.

54
00:06:05,917 --> 00:06:09,749
I thought I could lead him by the nose.

55
00:06:16,833 --> 00:06:19,874
Lord Wisnan, please forgive me.

56
00:06:23,500 --> 00:06:26,582
I'm four-months pregnant.

57
00:06:28,917 --> 00:06:33,624
What you did was a horrible insult
to my family! Revolting!

58
00:06:34,750 --> 00:06:39,082
Please, My lord!
I'd give you the moon and the stars,

59
00:06:39,500 --> 00:06:43,166
I'll give you anything!

60
00:06:43,625 --> 00:06:48,749
Just promise me that the scandal
will never leave this house.

61
00:06:51,750 --> 00:06:52,499
All right.

62
00:06:53,167 --> 00:06:54,916
State your wish.

63
00:06:55,458 --> 00:06:59,332
I want the ownership of everything,
the house, the land,

64
00:07:00,417 --> 00:07:04,332
and all the businesses in Bangkok
belonging to your family.

65
00:07:04,500 --> 00:07:08,791
That horrendous louse!

66
00:07:10,167 --> 00:07:14,624
What about my father, Jom?

67
00:07:16,292 --> 00:07:21,166
Where is he now?
What's happened to him?

68
00:07:22,292 --> 00:07:24,916
Don't suffer yourself

69
00:07:26,583 --> 00:07:28,582
with things of no great concern.

70
00:07:30,083 --> 00:07:33,041
What's gone is gone.

71
00:07:34,083 --> 00:07:36,916
Now you're here, my precious...

72
00:07:37,667 --> 00:07:41,666
so rest your body and mind.

73
00:07:42,375 --> 00:07:45,541
In the meantime, you and me...

74
00:07:46,292 --> 00:07:50,041
can plot sweet revenge against that

75
00:07:50,500 --> 00:07:54,457
scum you once called Father.

76
00:07:55,875 --> 00:08:02,749
How about that, my precious?

77
00:08:20,708 --> 00:08:26,416
Dear Hyacinth,
Ken and I have arrived safely in Phijit.

78
00:08:27,250 --> 00:08:29,166
We're staying with my grandmother,

79
00:08:29,792 --> 00:08:31,749
the only elder in the family

80
00:08:32,750 --> 00:08:36,416
who has always showed her kindness
towards me

81
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:38,707
since the day I was born.

82
00:08:39,917 --> 00:08:44,749
You must be wondering
why I had to leave home

83
00:08:45,250 --> 00:08:47,166
and come to Phijit in such haste.

84
00:08:47,750 --> 00:08:51,749
But if I had remained in Bangkok,

85
00:08:52,125 --> 00:08:54,916
I might've already been shot dead
like a rabid dog

86
00:08:55,250 --> 00:08:58,707
by the man whom
I always thought was my father.

87
00:08:59,875 --> 00:09:03,499
My life here is incredibly different
from my days in Bangkok.

88
00:09:04,125 --> 00:09:08,916
The air is fresh,

89
00:09:09,500 --> 00:09:11,249
the sky is clear,

90
00:09:11,917 --> 00:09:14,416
and everything seems so serene.

91
00:09:15,000 --> 00:09:18,457
For the first time in my life,
I feel completely free.

92
00:09:19,833 --> 00:09:23,291
I'm only concerned
about my virile friend, Ken.

93
00:09:23,583 --> 00:09:27,624
Because all the servants here
are wrinkled old ladies.

94
00:09:31,000 --> 00:09:33,249
Don't worry about me,

95
00:09:33,917 --> 00:09:36,457
I feel completely at peace here.

96
00:09:37,250 --> 00:09:40,332
Missing you always, Jan Dara.

97
00:09:42,583 --> 00:09:45,291
Master Jan,
I can't stand it any longer.

98
00:09:47,250 --> 00:09:50,082
Why? Work's too hard?

99
00:09:51,417 --> 00:09:52,749
Hard work my foot!

100
00:09:53,292 --> 00:09:55,832
Every day I make jasmine garlands,
carry water

101
00:09:56,125 --> 00:09:57,916
and cook with a bunch of old women!

102
00:09:58,583 --> 00:10:02,916
Master Jan,
I feel like my heart is withering.

103
00:10:03,042 --> 00:10:06,124
Like a tree dying for a drop
of magic water.

104
00:10:06,250 --> 00:10:10,082
What shall we do then?
This isn't like Bangkok.

105
00:10:10,167 --> 00:10:15,082
If we get naughty here,
Grandma will skin us alive.

106
00:10:15,208 --> 00:10:16,249
Aren't you afraid of her?

107
00:10:16,875 --> 00:10:19,957
I do! I'm shitting my pants!

108
00:10:20,750 --> 00:10:23,416
Your Grandma
is scarier than Lord Wisnan.

109
00:10:23,958 --> 00:10:28,291
But look,
I heard the servant boys talk about

110
00:10:28,417 --> 00:10:32,957
a certain establishment
with red and green lanterns.

111
00:10:33,833 --> 00:10:35,082
Don't you feel itchy?

112
00:10:36,333 --> 00:10:37,499
No.

113
00:10:38,250 --> 00:10:39,457
But I do!

114
00:10:39,750 --> 00:10:42,624
So I'd like to ask you
to sponsor my trip

115
00:10:42,917 --> 00:10:45,291
to the house of pleasure, just for once.

116
00:10:45,625 --> 00:10:47,499
I'd be eternally grateful.

117
00:10:47,917 --> 00:10:50,666
I have to let some steam off.

118
00:10:50,917 --> 00:10:53,166
My wrist is about to fall off!

119
00:10:58,417 --> 00:10:59,791
Take the whole purse.

120
00:11:27,417 --> 00:11:28,707
Good evening sir!

121
00:11:28,792 --> 00:11:30,749
I'm so sorry
but all the girls have been taken tonight.

122
00:11:30,833 --> 00:11:33,082
Except "Sister Patum",
not exactly young

123
00:11:33,208 --> 00:11:36,832
but her performance is legendary.

124
00:11:36,917 --> 00:11:38,416
Is that all talk?

125
00:11:38,500 --> 00:11:43,124
No sir! Patum never
lets her clients down, literally.

126
00:11:43,250 --> 00:11:47,166
Or you can wait for the young lasses,
but it'll be an hour.

127
00:11:52,250 --> 00:11:54,249
Patum it is then!

128
00:11:55,208 --> 00:11:57,082
Are you from Bangkok?

129
00:11:57,583 --> 00:11:58,541
Yes.

130
00:11:59,375 --> 00:12:00,999
Doing business?

131
00:12:02,458 --> 00:12:04,582
No, just staying.

132
00:12:05,792 --> 00:12:07,124
Where do you stay?

133
00:12:07,792 --> 00:12:13,332
Phijitvanich House at the edge of town.
Ever heard of it?

134
00:12:13,417 --> 00:12:15,207
Of course I do.

135
00:12:16,667 --> 00:12:20,416
I was a servant girl there.

136
00:12:21,750 --> 00:12:25,249
So you know the story of Dara,

137
00:12:25,750 --> 00:12:27,624
the lady who was raped.

138
00:12:32,250 --> 00:12:34,416
Miss Dara wasn't raped.

139
00:12:36,042 --> 00:12:38,457
It was the servant girl
who went with her

140
00:12:39,000 --> 00:12:40,291
who was raped.

141
00:12:42,000 --> 00:12:43,624
What're you talking about?

142
00:12:47,958 --> 00:12:52,082
Seventeen years ago
when Madame traveled with Miss Dara

143
00:12:52,792 --> 00:12:57,957
through the forest to visit her relatives
at a remote village,

144
00:12:58,250 --> 00:13:01,749
Jom and two other men

145
00:13:02,000 --> 00:13:04,541
ambushed them and kidnapped Dara

146
00:13:04,792 --> 00:13:09,249
and her 17-year-old servant girl
into their forest hideout.

147
00:13:10,167 --> 00:13:11,457
There...

148
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:20,707
The girl was brutally raped
by Jom's men

149
00:13:28,417 --> 00:13:32,499
while Jom himself was in the hut

150
00:13:32,583 --> 00:13:35,332
cooing with Dara like lovebirds.

151
00:13:36,583 --> 00:13:40,249
That servant girl was me.

152
00:13:42,417 --> 00:13:45,166
I was so scared back then.

153
00:13:45,250 --> 00:13:49,916
When those two fell asleep,

154
00:13:50,000 --> 00:13:52,041
I ran away to the police.

155
00:13:53,625 --> 00:13:55,707
What happened to that man, Jom?

156
00:13:56,625 --> 00:13:57,832
I don't know.

157
00:13:59,583 --> 00:14:03,249
I have never seen him again
since that day.

158
00:14:04,083 --> 00:14:08,749
But he didn't rape Dara,
I'm sure about that.

159
00:14:10,083 --> 00:14:12,207
Why do you want to know all of this?

160
00:14:13,583 --> 00:14:17,207
I never thought that
Ken's trip to the bawdy house

161
00:14:17,500 --> 00:14:22,624
would benefit me
with such a valuable tip-off.

162
00:14:23,083 --> 00:14:27,707
"Sister Patum",
who was once my mother's servant,

163
00:14:28,083 --> 00:14:30,832
pointed Ken to the Wiangchai House

164
00:14:30,917 --> 00:14:33,957
where my father, Jom, once lived.

165
00:14:34,417 --> 00:14:38,166
Most importantly, I learned that...

166
00:14:38,458 --> 00:14:41,416
I wasn't a child born
from a hideous circumstance

167
00:14:41,750 --> 00:14:45,207
as Lord Wisnan
had vengefully accused me of.

168
00:14:45,542 --> 00:14:49,499
They've moved to the Northeast!
How can we find them?

169
00:14:50,250 --> 00:14:54,707
Master Jan. Sister Patum also told me
about a police officer...

170
00:14:55,250 --> 00:14:59,499
Captain Ruang... something...

171
00:15:00,417 --> 00:15:03,166
Yes! Captain Ruangyos.
He was in charge of the case back then.

172
00:15:05,750 --> 00:15:09,707
I've gone through every case file
from 17 years ago.

173
00:15:10,917 --> 00:15:12,749
There was no such case as you mentioned.

174
00:15:13,750 --> 00:15:17,416
Nothing about the rape
and kidnapping of Miss Dara.

175
00:15:18,000 --> 00:15:19,957
And there wasn't any report

176
00:15:20,083 --> 00:15:22,163
about a shoot-out
between the police and the bandits.

177
00:15:22,875 --> 00:15:25,499
What about Captain Ruangyos?

178
00:15:27,000 --> 00:15:31,499
Captain Ruangyos...
left the force 17 years ago.

179
00:15:33,417 --> 00:15:38,624
That means
I'll never meet him again in this life.

180
00:15:51,958 --> 00:15:53,082
You do.

181
00:15:54,833 --> 00:15:58,291
Captain Ruangyos is my uncle.

182
00:16:06,333 --> 00:16:08,374
After he resigned,
he's spent his life in solitude,

183
00:16:08,792 --> 00:16:12,166
living a farmer's life in deep woods

184
00:16:12,583 --> 00:16:14,957
and barely visiting the town.

185
00:16:15,167 --> 00:16:17,916
Only I visit him sometimes.

186
00:16:18,417 --> 00:16:20,624
I can take you to see him

187
00:16:21,208 --> 00:16:24,791
but I'm not sure if he'll talk to you.

188
00:16:25,583 --> 00:16:26,749
He's Jan Dara,

189
00:16:27,708 --> 00:16:29,707
Lady Phijitraksa's grandson.

190
00:16:30,417 --> 00:16:32,416
He'd like to pay you respects.

191
00:16:41,917 --> 00:16:45,874
Please go back.
I have nothing to tell you.

192
00:16:52,667 --> 00:16:53,707
Wait sir.

193
00:17:01,417 --> 00:17:03,082
Please have mercy on me.

194
00:17:06,000 --> 00:17:09,291
In my whole life
I've never seen my father and mother.

195
00:17:10,625 --> 00:17:13,082
I only wish to know who my father is.

196
00:17:14,167 --> 00:17:15,957
And if he's doing fine.

197
00:17:16,917 --> 00:17:18,624
If he's still alive,

198
00:17:19,417 --> 00:17:21,582
I wish I could bow at his feet
at least once.

199
00:17:24,708 --> 00:17:26,148
Only then my soul would be at peace.

200
00:18:03,417 --> 00:18:05,124
You've come to the right place.

201
00:18:07,750 --> 00:18:09,499
I knew your mother...

202
00:18:11,375 --> 00:18:13,416
...and Jom very well.

203
00:18:24,458 --> 00:18:29,624
Actually I'd known Jom since we were
in a boarding school in Bangkok.

204
00:18:30,167 --> 00:18:35,624
I was his senior.
When his family in Phijit went bankrupt

205
00:18:36,208 --> 00:18:40,999
he quit school and came back here.
When I was transferred to Phijit,

206
00:18:41,292 --> 00:18:44,749
I visited him for old time's sake.

207
00:18:45,250 --> 00:18:47,374
Jom had changed a lot.

208
00:18:47,708 --> 00:18:54,166
He'd become a playboy.
Boozing, gambling, whoring...

209
00:18:54,625 --> 00:18:56,791
But he never hurt anyone.

210
00:18:57,667 --> 00:19:02,582
One day I was invited to
Miss Dara's homecoming ceremony

211
00:19:03,583 --> 00:19:06,749
when she arrived here from Bangkok.

212
00:19:07,375 --> 00:19:09,249
I admit that

213
00:19:10,417 --> 00:19:13,416
I fell hopelessly in love
with your mother at that instant.

214
00:19:15,125 --> 00:19:16,999
She was an image of perfection.

215
00:19:17,833 --> 00:19:20,707
Her fine, elegant manner...

216
00:19:20,917 --> 00:19:25,041
Her angelic face...

217
00:19:25,417 --> 00:19:26,749
That's why...

218
00:19:29,125 --> 00:19:31,124
when Patum reported to me

219
00:19:31,708 --> 00:19:35,666
that Dara was kidnapped
into the forest by Jom and his friends,

220
00:19:36,667 --> 00:19:39,374
I felt as if I were struck by lightning.

221
00:19:41,542 --> 00:19:42,957
How could that be possible?

222
00:19:45,250 --> 00:19:48,041
When Patum led me and your grandmother
to the forest hideout

223
00:19:48,875 --> 00:19:51,207
I found Jom's two lackeys

224
00:20:01,708 --> 00:20:03,791
and arrested them without any hassle.

225
00:20:03,917 --> 00:20:07,124
Then we found Miss Dara,
wretched and frail.

226
00:20:08,583 --> 00:20:10,416
But Jom was nowhere to be found.

227
00:20:11,083 --> 00:20:14,207
I conducted an investigation

228
00:20:14,292 --> 00:20:16,582
to find any clues that might lead to Jom.

229
00:20:17,083 --> 00:20:21,791
The two men confessed that
they raped Patum,

230
00:20:22,292 --> 00:20:26,124
while Jom and Miss Dara were talking
by the river.

231
00:20:28,875 --> 00:20:30,582
I want you to know now that

232
00:20:31,500 --> 00:20:34,499
I never want to hurt you.

233
00:20:36,125 --> 00:20:40,832
We're merely paying for the sin
committed by our parents.

234
00:20:41,333 --> 00:20:44,124
I'm the son...

235
00:20:45,375 --> 00:20:47,207
and my duty is to restore dignity

236
00:20:47,542 --> 00:20:50,624
and wealth taken from my family
by yours.

237
00:20:50,750 --> 00:20:52,416
Are you going to kill me?

238
00:20:54,583 --> 00:20:56,499
You have to bear my child.

239
00:20:57,708 --> 00:21:00,124
I hope you'd understand.

240
00:21:03,250 --> 00:21:05,041
If bearing your child...

241
00:21:07,208 --> 00:21:09,416
is a way to pay for the sin my family

242
00:21:10,083 --> 00:21:13,041
committed against yours...

243
00:21:14,750 --> 00:21:20,332
it's my duty too,

244
00:21:21,125 --> 00:21:24,582
to accept the karma forged
by my ancestors.

245
00:21:42,250 --> 00:21:43,749
I beg your forgiveness.

246
00:22:18,083 --> 00:22:22,916
But later that night,
after Patum ran away,

247
00:22:24,125 --> 00:22:25,916
things took a turn for the worst.

248
00:23:29,083 --> 00:23:31,957
After the two men raped Miss Dara,

249
00:23:32,333 --> 00:23:36,041
they dumped Jom's body into the river.

250
00:23:37,167 --> 00:23:39,541
Kill them now.

251
00:23:41,042 --> 00:23:43,041
Ma'am, by law we have to

252
00:23:43,125 --> 00:23:44,332
put them on trial.

253
00:23:44,708 --> 00:23:48,291
The law isn't the only means
to ensure justice,

254
00:23:48,917 --> 00:23:49,999
don't you agree?

255
00:24:03,083 --> 00:24:07,541
You're not my child!
You're a bastard!

256
00:24:08,500 --> 00:24:10,832
Your mother was raped!

257
00:24:11,583 --> 00:24:15,624
Why did I have to take you as my son!?

258
00:24:39,583 --> 00:24:41,707
Master Jan! Master Jan!

259
00:24:42,167 --> 00:24:42,999
What're you doing?!

260
00:24:43,708 --> 00:24:45,749
Get away from me!

